reviews.review_text:
This is very old classic restaurant. You get variety of food options here. They had divided into two sections, top floor serves non veg and bottom one serves veg only. Last time I visited, non veg section was closed. I had tried their veg thali which was good. All the items in the plate tasted really well including the chutney which added a unique flavour. Rajma prepared did not played well with my taste palette. Quantity of the items are fulfilling. They serve you two rotis and rice which will make you full for sure.
Overall a good thali.

Not worth the price and hype. Tried the fish thali there. It's priced at 250 rupees and I was not quite satisfied with the quality of fish and the taste as well. The stars of a thali are the rice, curry and fish and I was not happy with either of them. I am guessing they add soda to the rice which kinda bloats you up after the meal.

Next time, I tried their chicken fried rice and chilli chicken. 250 for chilli chicken and 180 rupees for fried rice would be great to pay if it was extraordinarily good. But the taste here was as good as a local Street side Chinese shop.

So nope from my side.

Only Veg restuarant is open. Non Veg is closed for now. Tried out the Makkan Peda and Famous Punjabi Samosa. Great taste. ðŸ‘Œ
